// ------------------------------------------------------------------
// NOTES ON REGULARIZATION
//
// Tikhonov (L2) regularization: Φ_reg = Φ + λ_reg * I
//   Small λ_reg (1e-6 to 1e-4): minimal smoothing, interpolates examples exactly.
//   Larger λ_reg (0.01 to 0.1): smoothing/approximation, more robust with noisy training data.
//
// For PSD correctives: use λ_reg ~ 1e-5; you want to hit examples exactly.
// For shape fitting:  use λ_reg ~ 1e-3; training data may have noise.
//
// POLYNOMIAL AUGMENTATION (for multiquadric, thin-plate spline):
// Augment Φ with rows/columns of [1, x1, x2, ..., xD] for consistency conditions.
// Adds D+1 unknowns; append zero rows to F for the polynomial constraints.
// Required for conditional positive-definiteness; see Fasshauer 2007.
// ------------------------------------------------------------------
